{"title_page": "Velaikkaran (2017 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2017 Indian Tamil-language drama film by Mohan Raja}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2017}}\n{{About|the 2017 film|other films|Velaikaran (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Velaikkaran\n| image          = Velaikkaran_Poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Mohan Raja]]\n| producer       = [[R. D. Raja]]\n| writer         = Mohan Raja<br>N. Baskaran\n| screenplay     = Mohan Raja<br>[[Subha (writers)|Subha]]\n| story          = Mohan Raja\n| starring       = [[Sivakarthikeyan]]<br>[[Fahadh Faasil]]<br>[[Nayanthara]]\n| music          = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| cinematography = [[Ramji]]\n| editing        = [[Anthony L. Ruben|Ruben]]\n| studio         = [[R. D. Raja|24AM Studios]]\n| distributor    = 24AM Studios<br />E4 Entertainment<br/>[[Fox Star Studios]]\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2017|12|22}}\n| runtime        = 160 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = 35 Crores <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/velaikkaran-box-office-collection-sivakarthikeyans-film-beats-remo-grosses-over-rs-50-crore-755460\n |title=Movie Velaikkaran Budget}}</ref>\n| gross          = 51 Crores <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/velaikkaran-box-office-collection-sivakarthikeyans-film-beats-remo-grosses-over-rs-50-crore-755460\n |title=Movie Velaikkaran Gross}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Velaikkaran''''' ({{literal translation|Worker}}) is a 2017 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[action thriller film]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/sivakarthikeyan-you-can-expect-a-lot-of-surprises-in-2018-news-tamil-rmvkeiadehhid.html|title=Sivakarthikeyan: You can expect a lot of surprises in 2018|publisher=Sify.com}}</ref> written and directed by [[Mohan Raja]]. The film stars [[Sivakarthikeyan]], [[Nayanthara]] and [[Fahadh Faasil]]. The film's music is composed by [[Anirudh Ravichander]], with cinematography by [[Ramji]]. Produced by [[R. D. Raja]], the film is based on a sales executive named Arivu (Sivakarthikeyan) who fights against food adulteration committed by high-class companies. The film was released on 22 December 2017.<ref>http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/velaikkaran-is-sivakarthikeyans-most-important-film-to-date-theres-a-lot-at-stake-for-the-rising-star-4268147.html</ref><ref>http://www.sify.com/movies/velaikkaran-review--an-honest-film-that-hits-the-right-notes-review-tamil-rmwljKdhcehdb.html</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n<!--per [[WP:FILMPLOT]], plot summaries should be between 400 and 700 words--> \nArivazhagan aka Arivu ([[Sivakarthikeyan]]) hails from Kolaikkara Kuppam a.k.a. Cooliekkara Kuppam, a [[slum]] area in [[Chennai]]. He is one such responsible youth who focuses on working for the betterment of his fellow beings, and he works hard for the same. Arivu starts Kuppam [[FM broadcasting|FM]] 90.8, a local radio channel with the help of the area gangster, Kasi ([[Prakash Raj]]). In reality, Arivu tries to free the people of the area from the atrocities of Kasi, who is deliberately preventing them from becoming independent, so that he may continue to dominate the area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/tamil/movies/velaikkaran-2017-velaikaran/story.html|title=Velaikkaran (Velaikaran) Preview, Velaikkaran Story & Synopsis, Velaikkaran Tamil Movie|website=FilmiBeat|language=en|access-date=2019-05-15}}</ref> Arivu succeeds in turning the people of the area against Kasi, thus destroying his support.\n\nLater, Arivu joins a leading [[FMCG]] company called Saffron and joins its sales department under Stella Bruce ([[Thambi Ramaiah]]). He manages to bring his friend Bhagya ([[Vijay Vasanth]]) out of Kasi's gang and gets him a job in Saffron. He meets Aadhi ([[Fahadh Faasil]]), Saffron's brand manager, who teaches him how to progress by doing smart work, and Arivu considers him as his inspiration. On the night of April 1, Kasi and his gang attack and stab Bhagya in Saffron's warehouse, whereupon he dies in Arivu's hands. Arivu, filled with rage, tries to attack Kasi, but Kasi's rival Doss ([[Sharath Lohitashwa]]) attacks and  stabs Kasi in retaliation for their previous encounter. Arivu admonishes Kasi for being a paid henchman. Kasi reveals to Arivu that he killed Bhagya on a contract given by Jayaram ([[Anish Kuruvilla]]), the President of Saffron. The motive was that Bhagya tried to help Kasthuri ([[Sneha]]), who filed a case claiming Saffron's products to be [[adulterant|adulterated]], due to which she lost her son. Arivu is addressed by Kasi as being a worse hitman than he himself is. Arivu then saves Kasi, who tells Arivu that all products manufactured by Saffron are adulterated. Arivu takes up a mission to fight such malpractices not only in Saffron, but in all the other five major food companies, including the one owned by Madhav Kurup ([[Mahesh Manjrekar]]). Arivu shares all of his plans with Aadhi. Meanwhile, is revealed that Aadhi is actually Adhiban Madhav, Madhav's son. He joined Saffron to know their trade secrets and merge the company with his father's company.\n\nArivu manages to convince his company's staff to manufacture products as per government regulations for two days. At the same time, he convinces the staff of the other companies to wear a kerchief on their dresses for the next two days, thus tricking the owners into believing that their workers have turned against them. However, Aadhi manages to foil Arivu's plan and [[coercion|coerces]] the other owners to write over the major shares of their company to Madhav, thus making him the deciding authority of all their companies. Aadhi manages to turn the employees against Arivu by tricking them into believing that Arivu worked as a spy for Madhav. Stella Bruce then slaps and humiliates Arivu, while Aadhi pretends to defend Arivu, claiming that he is innocent and that it is the new president who conspired all these. After this, Arivu reveals to Aadhi that Stella Bruce was his ally, and he now knows that Aadhi is the true traitor. Aadhi then burns down the godown containing the unadulterated products and reveals to Arivu that he is Madhav's son and will be the next CEO of the company. He also convinces the staff through his clever tactics and makes them propose his name as the new CEO, also revealing to Arivu that he will make them manufacture adulterated products without their knowledge, now that he commands their loyalty, support, and trust.\n\nArivu goes to the [[Radio Mirchi]] radio station on the night before May 1. He reveals that after the fire, one of the injured department heads of Saffron, Karpaga Vinayagam ([[Ramdoss]]), called him into the ambulance and told him that he followed the regulations on the third day too. Arivu learned from the other Saffron team workers - Kennedy ([[Mansoor Ali Khan (actor)|Mansoor Ali Khan]]), Vinoth ([[Kaali Venkat]]), Ansari ([[Aruldoss]]), and Sivaranjani ([[Vinodhini Vaidyanathan]]) - that after manufacturing quality products for two days, they could not bring themselves to manufacture adulterated products on the next day. They confirm they all followed government regulations, thus manufacturing quality products on the next day. Aadhi, now the CEO, hears the workers say that they will rebel against him and depose him if he tries to revert to manufacturing adulterated products. Arivu adds that the loyalty of all the employees in every field should not be wasted by showing it towards unethical employers. Aadhi then vents his frustration about the failure of his plan.\n\nAll the people in the city show their support to Arivu, who celebrates his success with his love interest Mrinalini ([[Nayanthara]]), friends, family, the people of his slum, and the people of the city as the film ends.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Sivakarthikeyan]] as Arivu\n* [[Fahadh Faasil]] as Adhiban Madhav (Aadhi)\n* [[Nayanthara]] as Mrinalini \"Miru\" (voice dubbed by [[Deepa Venkat]])\n* [[Prakash Raj]] as Kasi\n* [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]] as Kasthuri\n* [[Thambi Ramaiah]] as Stella Bruce\n* [[RJ Balaji]] as Sriram\n* [[Sathish]] as Hari\n* [[Vijay Vasanth]] as Bhagya\n* [[Robo Shankar]] as Chinna Thambi\n* [[Rohini (actress)|Rohini]] as Ponni\n* [[Charle]] as Murugesan\n* [[Ramdoss]] as Karpaga Vinayagam\n* [[Aruldoss]] as Ansari\n* [[Kaali Venkat]] as Vinoth\n* [[Mansoor Ali Khan (actor)|Mansoor Ali Khan]] as Kennedy\n* [[Vinodhini Vaidyanathan]] as Sivaranjani\n* [[Mime Gopi]] as Kishta\n* [[Y. G. Mahendra]] as Narayanan\n* [[Madhusudhan Rao (actor)|Madhusudhan Rao]] as Madhusudhan\n* [[Mahesh Manjrekar]] as Madhav Kurup\n* [[Sharath Lohitashwa]] as Doss\n* [[Anish Kuruvilla]] as Jayaram\n* [[Nagineedu]] as Loknath\n* [[Vivek Prasanna]] as Babu\n* [[Uday Mahesh]] as Naga Sudarshan\n* [[Balaji Venugopal]] as Saffron Assistant Senior Manager\n* [[Saravana Subbiah]] as TV Host\n* [[Maya S. Krishnan]] as Actress\n* Shyam Prasad as one of the Board of Directors\n* Vijayraj as Saffron Staff\n* Mithun Raj as Saffron Interview Candidate\n* Rajie Vijay Sarathy as Sriram's mother\n* Abdool as TV Stabilizer Salesman\n* Yuva Lakshmi as Vani\n* RJ Sha as himself in a special appearance\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\nIn December 2015, an official press announcement from producer [[R. D. Raja]] revealed that director [[Mohan Raja]] and [[Sivakarthikeyan]] would collaborate for his second production venture.<ref>{{cite web|author=Cinema Plus |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/sivakarthikeyan-teams-up-with-mohan-raja/article7981467.ece |title=Sivakarthikeyan teams up with Mohan Raja - Chennai |publisher=The Hindu |date= |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/mohan-raja-to-direct-sivakarthikeyan-news-tamil-pmlmvGiiecgag.html |title=Mohan Raja to direct Sivakarthikeyan! |publisher=Sify.com |date= |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> A launch event for the film was held on 11 March 2016, with the team announcing their intentions of starting the shoot in late 2016. \n=== Cast and crew ===\n[[Nayanthara]] signed the film in April 2016, in collaboration with Sivakarthikeyan, while Malayalam actor [[Fahadh Faasil]] was also brought in to appear in a pivotal role in the film, marking his debut in Tamil cinema.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-fahadh-faasil-thrilled-to-work-with-sivakarthikeyan-jayam-raja-2200850 |title=Fahadh Faasil thrilled to work with Sivakarthikeyan, Jayam Raja &#124; Latest News & Updates at Daily News & Analysis |publisher=Dnaindia.com |date=2016-04-11 |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/sivakarthikeyan-to-romance-nayanthara-in-mohan-rajas-next/1/634236.html |title=Sivakarthikeyan to romance Nayanthara in Mohan Raja's next : Regional cinema, News - India Today |publisher=Indiatoday.intoday.in |date=2016-04-03 |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> Prior to the start of shoot, several actors were finalised for supporting roles including [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]], [[Prakash Raj]], [[Rohini (actress)|Rohini]] and [[Thambi Ramaiah]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/thambi-ramaiah-on-being-a-part-of-mohan-rajas-next-with-sivakarthikeyan.html |title=Thambi Ramaiah on being a part of Mohan Raja's next with Sivakarthikeyan |publisher=Behindwoods.com |date=2016-10-16 |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/prakash-raj-on-board-for-mohan-raja-s-next-with-sivakarthikeyan-news-tamil-qjvlBNcfajfch.html |title=Prakash Raj on board for Mohan Raja`s next with Sivakarthikeyan! |publisher=Sify.com |date= |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Sneha-signs-Sivakartheyan-Mohan-Raja-film/articleshow/53943115.cms|title=Sneha signs Sivakartheyan-Mohan Raja film!|date=2016-08-31|website=Times of India|accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/rohini-to-play-sivakarthikeyans-mother-in-mohan-raja-directorial-film.html |title=Rohini to play Sivakarthikeyan's mother in Mohan Raja directorial film |publisher=Behindwoods.com |date=2016-11-03 |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> [[RJ Balaji]], [[Sathish]] also joined the cast.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/rj-balaji-and-sathish-confirmed-for-sivakarthikeyan-s-next-news-tnpsc-qisj02hhaffhj.html |title=RJ Balaji and Sathish confirmed for Sivakarthikeyan\u2019s next |publisher=Sify.com |date= |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> [[Anirudh Ravichander]], [[Vivek Harshan]] and [[T. Muthuraj]] joined the team as the music composer, editor and art director respectively. Likewise [[Anal Arasu]] was selected as the stunt choreographer, while Vishnu Govind and Sree Shankar were put in charge of sound editing and mixing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/anirudh-ravichander-to-score-music-for-sivakarthikeyan-mohan-raja-film-tamil-news-156985.html |title=Anirudh Ravichander to score music for Sivakarthikeyan Mohan Raja film - Tamil Movie News |publisher=Indiaglitz.com |date= |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> In a turn of events, editor [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]] replaces Vivek Harshan, which is evident on the latest film poster released for Deepavali season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/sivakarthikeyans-velaikkaran-has-a-change-of-editor.html |title=A Big Change In Sivarthikeyan's Velaikkaran Is Here! Check Out! |publisher=BehindWoods |date= |accessdate=2017-10-22}}</ref>\n=== Filming and post-production ===\nProduction started with the film as yet untitled in November 2016, in T Nagar, Chennai.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/sivakarthikeyan-mohan-raja-film-from-nov-11-news-tamil-qkok3Bdfjbccc.html |title=Sivakarthikeyan-Mohan Raja film from Nov 11 |publisher=Sify.com |date= |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> The shoot continued throughout January at Prasad Studios in Chennai where art director Muthuraj had erected a large set resembling Chennai's slums.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/sivakarthikeyan-mohan-raja-film-progresses-news-tamil-rcbsHEaadhafg.html |title=Sivakarthikeyan-Mohan Raja film progresses! |publisher=Sify.com |date= |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> In February 2017, Behindwoods reported that the film tentatively being given the title of ''Velaikkaran.'' This was after the team bought the title rights from [[Vijay Vasanth]] who had registered it for a future film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/sivakarthikeyans-next-film-has-been-tentatively-titled-as-velaikaran.html |title=Sivakarthikeyan\u2019s next film has been tentatively titled as Velaikaran |publisher=Behindwoods.com |date=2017-02-05 |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref><ref>http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/240217/vijay-vasanth-joins-sivakarthikeyan-and-nayanthara.html</ref> Behindwoods also reported that Fahadh Faasil would dub himself in Tamil in this movie, a first for him.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/fahadh-faasil-dubs-in-tamil-for-velaikkaran.html|title=Fahadh Faasil dubs in Tamil for Velaikkaran|date=2017-07-13|work=Behindwoods|access-date=2017-07-13}}</ref>\n\n==Music==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Velaikkaran\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 3 December 2017\n| recorded     = 2017\n| venue        = \n| studio       = Albuquerque Records, Chennai\n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 19:06\n| language     = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label        = [[Sony Music India|Sony Music]]\n| producer     = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| prev_title   = [[Vivegam]]\n| prev_year    = 2017\n| next_title   = [[Agnyaathavaasi]]\n| next_year    = 2017\n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Velaikkaran\n | type        = soundtrack\n | single1     = Karuthavanlaam Galeejaam\n | single1date = {{Start date|df=yes|2017|08|29}}\n | single2     = Iraiva + Uyire\n | single2date = {{Start date|df=yes|2017|11|02}}\n}}\n}}\n\nThe soundtrack album and background score of this film was composed by [[Anirudh Ravichander]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.movietet.com/movie-review/m/velaikkaran|title=Velaikkaran movie info - MovieTeT}}</ref> The album consists of five songs with [[Madhan Karky]] and [[Vivek (lyricist)|Vivek]] penning one song, and the rest of the songs were penned by [[Viveka (lyricist)|Viveka]].\n\nThe album was released by [[Sony Music India]]. The first single track \"Karuthavanlaam Galeejaam\" sung by Anirudh and written by Viveka was released on 28 August 2017, which picturises the life of the slum people, and also notes, that the lyrics intent to celebrate the working class and their contribution towards the development of the city.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/karuthavanlam-galeejam-song-velaikaran-celebrates-working-class-67625?amp|website=www.thenewsminute.com|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref> The song is filmed, in a huge set erected at [[Prasad Studios|Prasad Labs]], [[Chennai]] for a slum like concept. The second single was released on 2 November 2017. The combined single track \"Iraiva + Uyire\" sung by Anirudh and [[Jonita Gandhi]] consists of two songs \"Iraiva\" and \"Uyire\" which deals about love and life respectively. The song genres in these two of these, were alternatively different. While \"Iraiva\" is a solo number which consists of a slow melody with rock beats in between, \"Uyire\" is a slow enhancing duet, with beats involved in it. [[Sivakarthikeyan]] and [[Nayanthara]] went to [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] on September 2016, to shoot this duet in the picturesque locations of the country.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/velaikkaran-song-starring-siva-karthikeyan-and-nayanthara-iraiva-the-songs-transition-from-a-slow-romantic-beat-to-a-groovy-tune-is-kickass-1093723/|title=Velaikkaran song Iraiva:The song's transition from a slow romantic beat to a groovy tune is kickass!|date=2017-11-02|website=Bollywood Life|language=en-EN|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/velaikkaran-song-iraiva-this-sivakarthikeyan-nayanthara-song-is-high-on-life-and-love/story-mY06e2hqLTgV7E6HMMcJRK.html|title=Velaikkaran song Iraiva: This Sivakarthikeyan-Nayanthara song is high on life and love|date=2017-11-02|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n\nThe tracklist was released on 2 December 2017, through the official [[Twitter]] account of the production house.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/velaikkaran-tracklist-to-be-revealed-on-december-2.html|title=Velaikkaran tracklist to be revealed on December 2|date=2017-12-02|website=Behindwoods|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref> The audio launch event for the film was held on 3 December 2017 at [[ITC Grand Chola Hotel]] in [[Chennai]] where Sivakarthikeyan, [[Mohan Raja]] and Anirudh Ravichander along with other cast and crew, were present at the venue, while Nayanthara and [[Fahadh Faasil]] did not attend the audio launch. The event was streamed live on [[Facebook]], [[YouTube]] and [[Twitter]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/at-velaikkaran-audio-launch-sivakarthikeyan-vows-not-to-endorse-brands-and-act-in-ads-henceforth-4240725.html|title=At Velaikkaran audio launch, Sivakarthikeyan vows not to 'endorse brands and act in ads henceforth'- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=2017-12-04|website=Firstpost|language=en|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Velaikkaran Audio Launch Live {{!}} Anirudh {{!}} Sivakarthikeyan, Nayanthara l Mohan Raja|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KTV_mnPZbAE|language=en|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref> The songs were released simultaneously in other digital streaming platforms.<ref>{{Citation|title=Velaikkaran (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) by Anirudh Ravichander|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/velaikkaran-original-motion-picture-soundtrack/1320730090|language=en-us|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref> Later, the audio launch was telecasted on [[Star Vijay]] on 10 December 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/tamil/velaikkaran-audio-launch-to-be-aired-on-vijay-tv/articleshow/61980874.cms|title=Velaikkaran audio launch to be aired on Vijay TV - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/tamil/velaikkaran-audio-launch-on-vijay-tv-today/articleshow/62008426.cms|title=Velaikkaran audio launch on Vijay TV today - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n\n{{tracklist\n| extra_column = Singers\n| title1 = Karuthavanlaam Galeejam\n| lyrics1 = [[Viveka (lyricist)|Viveka]]\n| extra1 = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| length1 = 3:28\n| title2 = Iraiva\n| lyrics2 = Viveka\n| extra2 = [[Anirudh Ravichander]], [[Jonita Gandhi]]\n| length2 = 4:57\n| title3 = Vaa Velaikkara\n| lyrics3 = [[Vivek (lyricist)|Vivek]]\n| extra3 = [[Shakthisree Gopalan]], Bjorn Surrao\n| length3 = 2:35\n| title4 = Idhayane\n| lyrics4 = [[Madhan Karky]]\n| extra4 = Anirudh Ravichander, [[Neeti Mohan]]\n| length4 = 3:41\n| title5 = Ezhu Velaikkara\n| lyrics5 = Viveka\n| extra5 = [[Siddharth Mahadevan]]\n| length5 = 5:05\n| total_length = 19:06\n| all_writing = \n| title6 = \n| length6 = \n| title7 = \n| length7 = \n| title8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n| title11 = \n| length11 = \n| title12 = \n| length12 = \n| title13 = \n| length13 = \n| title14 = \n| length14 = \n| title15 = \n| length15 = \n| title16 = \n| length16 = \n| title17 = \n| length17 = \n| title18 = \n| length18 = \n| title19 = \n| length19 = \n| title20 = \n| length20 = \n}}\nThe album received positive reviews from critics. Behindwoods rated the album 3 out of 5 stars, with a quote \"Variety is the name of the game, and Anirudh is one of its best players!\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://m.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/velaikkaran/velaikkaran-songs-review.html|title=Velaikkaran (aka) Vellaikkaran Songs review|date=2017-12-03|website=Behindwoods|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref> OnlyKollywood rated 3.5 out of 5 stars, and stated \"Anirudh continues to deliver top quality music which is effortlessly innovative and makes for interesting listens. His ability to crack such a wide variety in a commercial film is his USP that's going to help in the long run. Velaikkaran is a colorful, energetic soundtrack that reflects good things in store for the film. The Anirudh - Sivakarthikeyan combo sparkles yet again.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.onlykollywood.com/velaikkaran-songs-review/|title=Velaikkaran Songs Review|date=2017-12-04|website=Only Kollywood|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref> Hindustan Times gave positive reviews stating \"Anirudh Ravichander delivers a box full of surprises\". Studioflicks rated 3.5 out of 5 and gave a verdict \"Sivakarthikeyan-Anirudh duo strikes gold again\" stating that \"Velaikkaran strikes spectacularly with three instant hits that includes Idhayane, Karuthavanlaam Galeejaam and Iraiva. The other tracks sounding like signature songs will definitely gain it impact with the visuals.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.studioflicks.com/reviews/velaikkaran-music-review/|title=Velaikkaran Music Review {{!}} Velaikkaran Songs Review {{!}} Studio Flicks|last=Sekar|date=2017-08-28|website=StudioFlicks|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nOn the first day of the film's shoot, the producer R. D. Raja revealed that the film would have a theatrical release on 25 August 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/release-date-of-sivakarthikeyan-mohan-raja-project-announced.html |title=Release date of Sivakarthikeyan - Mohan Raja project announced |publisher=Behindwoods.com |date=2016-11-11 |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> In April 2017, the production house has announced that the release date is postponed to 29 September 2017. Due to delays in post production the film's release date was shifted to the Christmas season, 22 December 2017.\nThe film is dubbed in [[Hindi language|Hindi]] as ''Ghayal Khiladi'' and released on [[YouTube]] on 6 January 2019 by Goldmines Telefilms.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4ZmBu9PtdZw&t=1959s</ref>\n\n===Marketing===\nThe first look poster was initially slated to release on 1 May 2017, coinciding with the Labour Day. But it was released on 5 June 2017,  which features Sivakarthikeyan as a marketing executive, with a bag in one hand and a knife in other hand. The second look poster of the film was released on 8 August 2017, on actor Fahadh Faasil's birthday, which features Sivakarthikeyan and Fahadh Faasil. Following this, the teaser of the film was released on 14 August 2017. A motion poster, describing the film's cast was released on 6 December 2017.\n\n== Box office==\nThe film collected over {{INRConvert|50|c}} at the worldwide box office.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/velaikkaran-box-office-collection-sivakarthikeyans-film-beats-remo-grosses-over-rs-50-crore-755460|title=Velaikkaran box office collection: Sivakarthikeyan's film grosses over Rs 50 crore|website=International Business Times|date=2018-01-03|access-date=2019-10-12}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nBaradwaj Rangan of Film Companion wrote \"The addressing of class in Tamil films is nothing new \u2013 and we know slum-resident Arivu (Sivakarthikeyan) is going to run a scratch across these rich men\u2019s lives \u2013 but the dignity in this film is. It wants to be a crowd-pleaser, but with class.\"<ref>https://www.filmcompanion.in/velaikkaran-movie-review/</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=7019820}}\n\n{{M. Raja}}\n[[Category:2017 films]]\n[[Category:2010s action thriller films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Chennai]]\n[[Category:Indian action thriller films]]\n[[Category:Indian drama films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Anirudh Ravichander]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Mohan Raja]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Films about social issues in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2017 Indian Tamil-language drama film by Mohan Raja}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2017}}\n{{About|the 2017 film|other films|Velaikaran (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Velaikkaran\n| image          = Velaikkaran_Poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Mohan Raja]]\n| producer       = [[R. D. Raja]]\n| writer         = Mohan Raja<br>N. Baskaran\n| screenplay     = Mohan Raja<br>[[Subha (writers)|Subha]]\n| story          = Mohan Raja\n| starring       = [[Sivakarthikeyan]]<br>[[Fahadh Faasil]]<br>[[Nayanthara]]\n| music          = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| cinematography = [[Ramji]]\n| editing        = [[Anthony L. Ruben|Ruben]]\n| studio         = [[R. D. Raja|24AM Studios]]\n| distributor    = 24AM Studios<br />E4 Entertainment<br/>[[Fox Star Studios]]\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2017|12|22}}\n| runtime        = 160 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = <!--Must cite a reliable published source with a reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb. no fan-sites.-->\n| gross          = <!--Must cite a reliable published source with a reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb. no fan-sites.-->\n}}\n\n'''''Velaikkaran''''' ({{literal translation|Worker}}) is a 2017 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[action thriller film]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/sivakarthikeyan-you-can-expect-a-lot-of-surprises-in-2018-news-tamil-rmvkeiadehhid.html|title=Sivakarthikeyan: You can expect a lot of surprises in 2018|publisher=Sify.com}}</ref> written and directed by [[Mohan Raja]]. The film stars [[Sivakarthikeyan]], [[Nayanthara]] and [[Fahadh Faasil]]. The film's music is composed by [[Anirudh Ravichander]], with cinematography by [[Ramji]]. Produced by [[R. D. Raja]], the film is based on a sales executive named Arivu (Sivakarthikeyan) who fights against food adulteration committed by high-class companies. The film was released on 22 December 2017.<ref>http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/velaikkaran-is-sivakarthikeyans-most-important-film-to-date-theres-a-lot-at-stake-for-the-rising-star-4268147.html</ref><ref>http://www.sify.com/movies/velaikkaran-review--an-honest-film-that-hits-the-right-notes-review-tamil-rmwljKdhcehdb.html</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n<!--per [[WP:FILMPLOT]], plot summaries should be between 400 and 700 words--> \nArivazhagan aka Arivu ([[Sivakarthikeyan]]) hails from Kolaikkara Kuppam a.k.a. Cooliekkara Kuppam, a [[slum]] area in [[Chennai]]. He is one such responsible youth who focuses on working for the betterment of his fellow beings, and he works hard for the same. Arivu starts Kuppam [[FM broadcasting|FM]] 90.8, a local radio channel with the help of the area gangster, Kasi ([[Prakash Raj]]). In reality, Arivu tries to free the people of the area from the atrocities of Kasi, who is deliberately preventing them from becoming independent, so that he may continue to dominate the area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/tamil/movies/velaikkaran-2017-velaikaran/story.html|title=Velaikkaran (Velaikaran) Preview, Velaikkaran Story & Synopsis, Velaikkaran Tamil Movie|website=FilmiBeat|language=en|access-date=2019-05-15}}</ref> Arivu succeeds in turning the people of the area against Kasi, thus destroying his support.\n\nLater, Arivu joins a leading [[FMCG]] company called Saffron and joins its sales department under Stella Bruce ([[Thambi Ramaiah]]). He manages to bring his friend Bhagya ([[Vijay Vasanth]]) out of Kasi's gang and gets him a job in Saffron. He meets Aadhi ([[Fahadh Faasil]]), Saffron's brand manager, who teaches him how to progress by doing smart work, and Arivu considers him as his inspiration. On the night of April 1, Kasi and his gang attack and stab Bhagya in Saffron's warehouse, whereupon he dies in Arivu's hands. Arivu, filled with rage, tries to attack Kasi, but Kasi's rival Doss ([[Sharath Lohitashwa]]) attacks and  stabs Kasi in retaliation for their previous encounter. Arivu admonishes Kasi for being a paid henchman. Kasi reveals to Arivu that he killed Bhagya on a contract given by Jayaram ([[Anish Kuruvilla]]), the President of Saffron. The motive was that Bhagya tried to help Kasthuri ([[Sneha]]), who filed a case claiming Saffron's products to be [[adulterant|adulterated]], due to which she lost her son. Arivu is addressed by Kasi as being a worse hitman than he himself is. Arivu then saves Kasi, who tells Arivu that all products manufactured by Saffron are adulterated. Arivu takes up a mission to fight such malpractices not only in Saffron, but in all the other five major food companies, including the one owned by Madhav Kurup ([[Mahesh Manjrekar]]). Arivu shares all of his plans with Aadhi. Meanwhile, is revealed that Aadhi is actually Adhiban Madhav, Madhav's son. He joined Saffron to know their trade secrets and merge the company with his father's company.\n\nArivu manages to convince his company's staff to manufacture products as per government regulations for two days. At the same time, he convinces the staff of the other companies to wear a kerchief on their dresses for the next two days, thus tricking the owners into believing that their workers have turned against them. However, Aadhi manages to foil Arivu's plan and [[coercion|coerces]] the other owners to write over the major shares of their company to Madhav, thus making him the deciding authority of all their companies. Aadhi manages to turn the employees against Arivu by tricking them into believing that Arivu worked as a spy for Madhav. Stella Bruce then slaps and humiliates Arivu, while Aadhi pretends to defend Arivu, claiming that he is innocent and that it is the new president who conspired all these. After this, Arivu reveals to Aadhi that Stella Bruce was his ally, and he now knows that Aadhi is the true traitor. Aadhi then burns down the godown containing the unadulterated products and reveals to Arivu that he is Madhav's son and will be the next CEO of the company. He also convinces the staff through his clever tactics and makes them propose his name as the new CEO, also revealing to Arivu that he will make them manufacture adulterated products without their knowledge, now that he commands their loyalty, support, and trust.\n\nArivu goes to the [[Radio Mirchi]] radio station on the night before May 1. He reveals that after the fire, one of the injured department heads of Saffron, Karpaga Vinayagam ([[Ramdoss]]), called him into the ambulance and told him that he followed the regulations on the third day too. Arivu learned from the other Saffron team workers - Kennedy ([[Mansoor Ali Khan (actor)|Mansoor Ali Khan]]), Vinoth ([[Kaali Venkat]]), Ansari ([[Aruldoss]]), and Sivaranjani ([[Vinodhini Vaidyanathan]]) - that after manufacturing quality products for two days, they could not bring themselves to manufacture adulterated products on the next day. They confirm they all followed government regulations, thus manufacturing quality products on the next day. Aadhi, now the CEO, hears the workers say that they will rebel against him and depose him if he tries to revert to manufacturing adulterated products. Arivu adds that the loyalty of all the employees in every field should not be wasted by showing it towards unethical employers. Aadhi then vents his frustration about the failure of his plan.\n\nAll the people in the city show their support to Arivu, who celebrates his success with his love interest Mrinalini ([[Nayanthara]]), friends, family, the people of his slum, and the people of the city as the film ends.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Sivakarthikeyan]] as Arivu\n* [[Fahadh Faasil]] as Adhiban Madhav (Aadhi)\n* [[Nayanthara]] as Mrinalini \"Miru\" (voice dubbed by [[Deepa Venkat]])\n* [[Prakash Raj]] as Kasi\n* [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]] as Kasthuri\n* [[Thambi Ramaiah]] as Stella Bruce\n* [[RJ Balaji]] as Sriram\n* [[Sathish]] as Hari\n* [[Vijay Vasanth]] as Bhagya\n* [[Robo Shankar]] as Chinna Thambi\n* [[Rohini (actress)|Rohini]] as Ponni\n* [[Charle]] as Murugesan\n* [[Ramdoss]] as Karpaga Vinayagam\n* [[Aruldoss]] as Ansari\n* [[Kaali Venkat]] as Vinoth\n* [[Mansoor Ali Khan (actor)|Mansoor Ali Khan]] as Kennedy\n* [[Vinodhini Vaidyanathan]] as Sivaranjani\n* [[Mime Gopi]] as Kishta\n* [[Y. G. Mahendra]] as Narayanan\n* [[Madhusudhan Rao (actor)|Madhusudhan Rao]] as Madhusudhan\n* [[Mahesh Manjrekar]] as Madhav Kurup\n* [[Sharath Lohitashwa]] as Doss\n* [[Anish Kuruvilla]] as Jayaram\n* [[Nagineedu]] as Loknath\n* [[Vivek Prasanna]] as Babu\n* [[Uday Mahesh]] as Naga Sudarshan\n* [[Balaji Venugopal]] as Saffron Assistant Senior Manager\n* [[Saravana Subbiah]] as TV Host\n* [[Maya S. Krishnan]] as Actress\n* Shyam Prasad as one of the Board of Directors\n* Vijayraj as Saffron Staff\n* Mithun Raj as Saffron Interview Candidate\n* Rajie Vijay Sarathy as Sriram's mother\n* Abdool as TV Stabilizer Salesman\n* Yuva Lakshmi as Vani\n* RJ Sha as himself in a special appearance\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\nIn December 2015, an official press announcement from producer [[R. D. Raja]] revealed that director [[Mohan Raja]] and [[Sivakarthikeyan]] would collaborate for his second production venture.<ref>{{cite web|author=Cinema Plus |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/sivakarthikeyan-teams-up-with-mohan-raja/article7981467.ece |title=Sivakarthikeyan teams up with Mohan Raja - Chennai |publisher=The Hindu |date= |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/mohan-raja-to-direct-sivakarthikeyan-news-tamil-pmlmvGiiecgag.html |title=Mohan Raja to direct Sivakarthikeyan! |publisher=Sify.com |date= |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> A launch event for the film was held on 11 March 2016, with the team announcing their intentions of starting the shoot in late 2016. \n=== Cast and crew ===\n[[Nayanthara]] signed the film in April 2016, in collaboration with Sivakarthikeyan, while Malayalam actor [[Fahadh Faasil]] was also brought in to appear in a pivotal role in the film, marking his debut in Tamil cinema.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-fahadh-faasil-thrilled-to-work-with-sivakarthikeyan-jayam-raja-2200850 |title=Fahadh Faasil thrilled to work with Sivakarthikeyan, Jayam Raja &#124; Latest News & Updates at Daily News & Analysis |publisher=Dnaindia.com |date=2016-04-11 |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/sivakarthikeyan-to-romance-nayanthara-in-mohan-rajas-next/1/634236.html |title=Sivakarthikeyan to romance Nayanthara in Mohan Raja's next : Regional cinema, News - India Today |publisher=Indiatoday.intoday.in |date=2016-04-03 |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> Prior to the start of shoot, several actors were finalised for supporting roles including [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]], [[Prakash Raj]], [[Rohini (actress)|Rohini]] and [[Thambi Ramaiah]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/thambi-ramaiah-on-being-a-part-of-mohan-rajas-next-with-sivakarthikeyan.html |title=Thambi Ramaiah on being a part of Mohan Raja's next with Sivakarthikeyan |publisher=Behindwoods.com |date=2016-10-16 |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/prakash-raj-on-board-for-mohan-raja-s-next-with-sivakarthikeyan-news-tamil-qjvlBNcfajfch.html |title=Prakash Raj on board for Mohan Raja`s next with Sivakarthikeyan! |publisher=Sify.com |date= |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Sneha-signs-Sivakartheyan-Mohan-Raja-film/articleshow/53943115.cms|title=Sneha signs Sivakartheyan-Mohan Raja film!|date=2016-08-31|website=Times of India|accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/rohini-to-play-sivakarthikeyans-mother-in-mohan-raja-directorial-film.html |title=Rohini to play Sivakarthikeyan's mother in Mohan Raja directorial film |publisher=Behindwoods.com |date=2016-11-03 |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> [[RJ Balaji]], [[Sathish]] also joined the cast.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/rj-balaji-and-sathish-confirmed-for-sivakarthikeyan-s-next-news-tnpsc-qisj02hhaffhj.html |title=RJ Balaji and Sathish confirmed for Sivakarthikeyan\u2019s next |publisher=Sify.com |date= |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> [[Anirudh Ravichander]], [[Vivek Harshan]] and [[T. Muthuraj]] joined the team as the music composer, editor and art director respectively. Likewise [[Anal Arasu]] was selected as the stunt choreographer, while Vishnu Govind and Sree Shankar were put in charge of sound editing and mixing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/anirudh-ravichander-to-score-music-for-sivakarthikeyan-mohan-raja-film-tamil-news-156985.html |title=Anirudh Ravichander to score music for Sivakarthikeyan Mohan Raja film - Tamil Movie News |publisher=Indiaglitz.com |date= |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> In a turn of events, editor [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]] replaces Vivek Harshan, which is evident on the latest film poster released for Deepavali season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/sivakarthikeyans-velaikkaran-has-a-change-of-editor.html |title=A Big Change In Sivarthikeyan's Velaikkaran Is Here! Check Out! |publisher=BehindWoods |date= |accessdate=2017-10-22}}</ref>\n=== Filming and post-production ===\nProduction started with the film as yet untitled in November 2016, in T Nagar, Chennai.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/sivakarthikeyan-mohan-raja-film-from-nov-11-news-tamil-qkok3Bdfjbccc.html |title=Sivakarthikeyan-Mohan Raja film from Nov 11 |publisher=Sify.com |date= |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> The shoot continued throughout January at Prasad Studios in Chennai where art director Muthuraj had erected a large set resembling Chennai's slums.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/sivakarthikeyan-mohan-raja-film-progresses-news-tamil-rcbsHEaadhafg.html |title=Sivakarthikeyan-Mohan Raja film progresses! |publisher=Sify.com |date= |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> In February 2017, Behindwoods reported that the film tentatively being given the title of ''Velaikkaran.'' This was after the team bought the title rights from [[Vijay Vasanth]] who had registered it for a future film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/sivakarthikeyans-next-film-has-been-tentatively-titled-as-velaikaran.html |title=Sivakarthikeyan\u2019s next film has been tentatively titled as Velaikaran |publisher=Behindwoods.com |date=2017-02-05 |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref><ref>http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/240217/vijay-vasanth-joins-sivakarthikeyan-and-nayanthara.html</ref> Behindwoods also reported that Fahadh Faasil would dub himself in Tamil in this movie, a first for him.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/fahadh-faasil-dubs-in-tamil-for-velaikkaran.html|title=Fahadh Faasil dubs in Tamil for Velaikkaran|date=2017-07-13|work=Behindwoods|access-date=2017-07-13}}</ref>\n\n==Music==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Velaikkaran\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 3 December 2017\n| recorded     = 2017\n| venue        = \n| studio       = Albuquerque Records, Chennai\n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 19:06\n| language     = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label        = [[Sony Music India|Sony Music]]\n| producer     = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| prev_title   = [[Vivegam]]\n| prev_year    = 2017\n| next_title   = [[Agnyaathavaasi]]\n| next_year    = 2017\n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Velaikkaran\n | type        = soundtrack\n | single1     = Karuthavanlaam Galeejaam\n | single1date = {{Start date|df=yes|2017|08|29}}\n | single2     = Iraiva + Uyire\n | single2date = {{Start date|df=yes|2017|11|02}}\n}}\n}}\n\nThe soundtrack album and background score of this film was composed by [[Anirudh Ravichander]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.movietet.com/movie-review/m/velaikkaran|title=Velaikkaran movie info - MovieTeT}}</ref> The album consists of five songs with [[Madhan Karky]] and [[Vivek (lyricist)|Vivek]] penning one song, and the rest of the songs were penned by [[Viveka (lyricist)|Viveka]].\n\nThe album was released by [[Sony Music India]]. The first single track \"Karuthavanlaam Galeejaam\" sung by Anirudh and written by Viveka was released on 28 August 2017, which picturises the life of the slum people, and also notes, that the lyrics intent to celebrate the working class and their contribution towards the development of the city.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/karuthavanlam-galeejam-song-velaikaran-celebrates-working-class-67625?amp|website=www.thenewsminute.com|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref> The song is filmed, in a huge set erected at [[Prasad Studios|Prasad Labs]], [[Chennai]] for a slum like concept. The second single was released on 2 November 2017. The combined single track \"Iraiva + Uyire\" sung by Anirudh and [[Jonita Gandhi]] consists of two songs \"Iraiva\" and \"Uyire\" which deals about love and life respectively. The song genres in these two of these, were alternatively different. While \"Iraiva\" is a solo number which consists of a slow melody with rock beats in between, \"Uyire\" is a slow enhancing duet, with beats involved in it. [[Sivakarthikeyan]] and [[Nayanthara]] went to [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] on September 2016, to shoot this duet in the picturesque locations of the country.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/velaikkaran-song-starring-siva-karthikeyan-and-nayanthara-iraiva-the-songs-transition-from-a-slow-romantic-beat-to-a-groovy-tune-is-kickass-1093723/|title=Velaikkaran song Iraiva:The song's transition from a slow romantic beat to a groovy tune is kickass!|date=2017-11-02|website=Bollywood Life|language=en-EN|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/velaikkaran-song-iraiva-this-sivakarthikeyan-nayanthara-song-is-high-on-life-and-love/story-mY06e2hqLTgV7E6HMMcJRK.html|title=Velaikkaran song Iraiva: This Sivakarthikeyan-Nayanthara song is high on life and love|date=2017-11-02|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n\nThe tracklist was released on 2 December 2017, through the official [[Twitter]] account of the production house.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/velaikkaran-tracklist-to-be-revealed-on-december-2.html|title=Velaikkaran tracklist to be revealed on December 2|date=2017-12-02|website=Behindwoods|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref> The audio launch event for the film was held on 3 December 2017 at [[ITC Grand Chola Hotel]] in [[Chennai]] where Sivakarthikeyan, [[Mohan Raja]] and Anirudh Ravichander along with other cast and crew, were present at the venue, while Nayanthara and [[Fahadh Faasil]] did not attend the audio launch. The event was streamed live on [[Facebook]], [[YouTube]] and [[Twitter]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/at-velaikkaran-audio-launch-sivakarthikeyan-vows-not-to-endorse-brands-and-act-in-ads-henceforth-4240725.html|title=At Velaikkaran audio launch, Sivakarthikeyan vows not to 'endorse brands and act in ads henceforth'- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=2017-12-04|website=Firstpost|language=en|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Velaikkaran Audio Launch Live {{!}} Anirudh {{!}} Sivakarthikeyan, Nayanthara l Mohan Raja|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KTV_mnPZbAE|language=en|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref> The songs were released simultaneously in other digital streaming platforms.<ref>{{Citation|title=Velaikkaran (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) by Anirudh Ravichander|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/velaikkaran-original-motion-picture-soundtrack/1320730090|language=en-us|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref> Later, the audio launch was telecasted on [[Star Vijay]] on 10 December 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/tamil/velaikkaran-audio-launch-to-be-aired-on-vijay-tv/articleshow/61980874.cms|title=Velaikkaran audio launch to be aired on Vijay TV - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/tamil/velaikkaran-audio-launch-on-vijay-tv-today/articleshow/62008426.cms|title=Velaikkaran audio launch on Vijay TV today - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n\n{{tracklist\n| extra_column = Singers\n| title1 = Karuthavanlaam Galeejam\n| lyrics1 = [[Viveka (lyricist)|Viveka]]\n| extra1 = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| length1 = 3:28\n| title2 = Iraiva\n| lyrics2 = Viveka\n| extra2 = [[Anirudh Ravichander]], [[Jonita Gandhi]]\n| length2 = 4:57\n| title3 = Vaa Velaikkara\n| lyrics3 = [[Vivek (lyricist)|Vivek]]\n| extra3 = [[Shakthisree Gopalan]], Bjorn Surrao\n| length3 = 2:35\n| title4 = Idhayane\n| lyrics4 = [[Madhan Karky]]\n| extra4 = Anirudh Ravichander, [[Neeti Mohan]]\n| length4 = 3:41\n| title5 = Ezhu Velaikkara\n| lyrics5 = Viveka\n| extra5 = [[Siddharth Mahadevan]]\n| length5 = 5:05\n| total_length = 19:06\n| all_writing = \n| title6 = \n| length6 = \n| title7 = \n| length7 = \n| title8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n| title11 = \n| length11 = \n| title12 = \n| length12 = \n| title13 = \n| length13 = \n| title14 = \n| length14 = \n| title15 = \n| length15 = \n| title16 = \n| length16 = \n| title17 = \n| length17 = \n| title18 = \n| length18 = \n| title19 = \n| length19 = \n| title20 = \n| length20 = \n}}\nThe album received positive reviews from critics. Behindwoods rated the album 3 out of 5 stars, with a quote \"Variety is the name of the game, and Anirudh is one of its best players!\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://m.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/velaikkaran/velaikkaran-songs-review.html|title=Velaikkaran (aka) Vellaikkaran Songs review|date=2017-12-03|website=Behindwoods|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref> OnlyKollywood rated 3.5 out of 5 stars, and stated \"Anirudh continues to deliver top quality music which is effortlessly innovative and makes for interesting listens. His ability to crack such a wide variety in a commercial film is his USP that's going to help in the long run. Velaikkaran is a colorful, energetic soundtrack that reflects good things in store for the film. The Anirudh - Sivakarthikeyan combo sparkles yet again.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.onlykollywood.com/velaikkaran-songs-review/|title=Velaikkaran Songs Review|date=2017-12-04|website=Only Kollywood|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref> Hindustan Times gave positive reviews stating \"Anirudh Ravichander delivers a box full of surprises\". Studioflicks rated 3.5 out of 5 and gave a verdict \"Sivakarthikeyan-Anirudh duo strikes gold again\" stating that \"Velaikkaran strikes spectacularly with three instant hits that includes Idhayane, Karuthavanlaam Galeejaam and Iraiva. The other tracks sounding like signature songs will definitely gain it impact with the visuals.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.studioflicks.com/reviews/velaikkaran-music-review/|title=Velaikkaran Music Review {{!}} Velaikkaran Songs Review {{!}} Studio Flicks|last=Sekar|date=2017-08-28|website=StudioFlicks|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nOn the first day of the film's shoot, the producer R. D. Raja revealed that the film would have a theatrical release on 25 August 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/release-date-of-sivakarthikeyan-mohan-raja-project-announced.html |title=Release date of Sivakarthikeyan - Mohan Raja project announced |publisher=Behindwoods.com |date=2016-11-11 |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> In April 2017, the production house has announced that the release date is postponed to 29 September 2017. Due to delays in post production the film's release date was shifted to the Christmas season, 22 December 2017.\nThe film is dubbed in [[Hindi language|Hindi]] as ''Ghayal Khiladi'' and released on [[YouTube]] on 6 January 2019 by Goldmines Telefilms.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4ZmBu9PtdZw&t=1959s</ref>\n\n===Marketing===\nThe first look poster was initially slated to release on 1 May 2017, coinciding with the Labour Day. But it was released on 5 June 2017,  which features Sivakarthikeyan as a marketing executive, with a bag in one hand and a knife in other hand. The second look poster of the film was released on 8 August 2017, on actor Fahadh Faasil's birthday, which features Sivakarthikeyan and Fahadh Faasil. Following this, the teaser of the film was released on 14 August 2017. A motion poster, describing the film's cast was released on 6 December 2017.\n\n== Box office==\nThe film collected over {{INRConvert|50|c}} at the worldwide box office.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/velaikkaran-box-office-collection-sivakarthikeyans-film-beats-remo-grosses-over-rs-50-crore-755460|title=Velaikkaran box office collection: Sivakarthikeyan's film grosses over Rs 50 crore|website=International Business Times|date=2018-01-03|access-date=2019-10-12}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nBaradwaj Rangan of Film Companion wrote \"The addressing of class in Tamil films is nothing new \u2013 and we know slum-resident Arivu (Sivakarthikeyan) is going to run a scratch across these rich men\u2019s lives \u2013 but the dignity in this film is. It wants to be a crowd-pleaser, but with class.\"<ref>https://www.filmcompanion.in/velaikkaran-movie-review/</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=7019820}}\n\n{{M. Raja}}\n[[Category:2017 films]]\n[[Category:2010s action thriller films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Chennai]]\n[[Category:Indian action thriller films]]\n[[Category:Indian drama films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Anirudh Ravichander]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Mohan Raja]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Films about social issues in India]]\n", "name_user": "Thinkwiki", "label": "safe", "comment": "Budget and Gross update", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Velaikkaran_(2017_film)"}
{"title_page": "Yoav Shechtman", "text_new": "{{Infobox scientist\n|name        = Yoav Shechtman\n|native_name = \u05d9\u05d5\u05d0\u05d1 \u05e9\u05db\u05d8\u05de\u05df\n|image       = \n|caption     = \n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1980|3|17|df=y}}\n|birth_place = [[Haifa, Israel]]\n|nationality = Israeli\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|alma_mater  = {{hlist|[[Technion \u2013 Israel Institute of Technology|Technion]]|[[Stanford University]]}}\n|field       = [[Biomedical Engineering]]\n|work_institution = [[Technion \u2013 Israel Institute of Technology|Technion]]\n|known_for    = {{hlist|[[Nanobiotechnology]]|[[Super-resolution microscopy]]}}\n| prizes       = \n| doctoral_advisors = Mordechai Segev<br />[[Yonina Eldar]]\n| academic_advisors = [[William E. Moerner]]\n|spouse       = Tamar Navrotsky Shechtman\n}}\n'''Prof. Yoav Shechtman''' ({{lang-he-n|\u05d9\u05d5\u05d0\u05d1 \u05e9\u05db\u05d8\u05de\u05df}}; born March 17, 1980) is an Israeli physicist. He currently heads the Nano-Bio-Optics lab at the [[Technion \u2013 Israel Institute of Technology]]. Yoav Shechtman is the son of [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel prize]] laureate, [[Dan Shechtman]].<ref name=\"iupab\">{{cite web|url=http://iupab.org/2020/04/04/the-first-edition-of-the-iupab-young-investigator-prize-has-been-awarded-to-dr-yoav-shechtman/|title=The first Edition of the IUPAB Young Investigator Medal and Prize has been awarded to Dr Yoav Shechtman|date=4 April 2020|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"grapevine\">{{cite web|url=https://www.fromthegrapevine.com/innovation/mortimer-zuckerman-stem-institute-lucien-weiss-technion-israel|title=$100 million grant lets students study STEM for free in this country|first=Benyamin|last=Cohen|publisher=From The Grapevine|date=8 April 2019|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nYoav Shechtman was born on March 17, 1980 to Tzipora and [[Dan Shechtman]].<ref name=\"grapevine\" />\n\n==Academic career==\nShechtman holds a BSc in Physics and Electrical Engineering (2007) and a Phd in Physics (2013) which he acquired from the [[Technion]]. He later completed a postdoc at [[Stanford University]] (2016), developing [[super-resolution microscopy]] methods with [[W.E. Moerner]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://biomed.faculty-ms.technion.ac.il/members/yoav-shechtman/|title=Yoav Shechtman - Technion Faculty of Biomedical Engineering|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nSince October 2016, Shechtman is a faculty member in the [[Technion-Israel Institute of Technology]] where he currently heads the Nano-Bio-Optics lab which focuses on developing methods for molecular identification and optical imaging modalities in addition to developing [[machine learning]] tools for efficient imaging reconstruction in applications such as high spatio-temopral resolution tracking of biomolecules in three dimensions and in multiple colors inside live cells.<ref name=\"makor-rishon\">{{cite web|language=he|url=https://www.makorrishon.co.il/magazine/219665/|title=Foam for the Lungs and Self Diagnosis: The Faculty Which Diverted to Corona|first=Yael|last=Froind Avraham|publisher=[[Makor Rishon]]|date=7 April 2020|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"ismbe\">{{cite web|url=https://ismbe.org.il/announcements/|title=Israel Society for Medical and Biological Engineering - Announcements|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Shechtman and his team at the Technion developed an efficient method for bio imaging in super resolution.<ref name=\"hayadan\">{{cite web|language=he|url=https://www.hayadan.org.il/life-in-super-resolution-0206182|title=Life in Super Resolution|publisher=HaYadan|date=2 June 2018|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n* 2016 Technion Career Advancement Chair\n* 2017 Zuckerman Faculty Scholar\n* 2018 Early Career Award of the International Association for Medical and Biological Engineering (IAMBE)\n* 2018 European Research Council starting grant\n* 2019 Uzi and Michal Halevy Award for Innovative Applied Engineering\n* 2020 IUPAB Young Investigator Medal and Prize<ref name=\"iupab\" />\n\n==Published works==\n* {{Cite journal\n | author = [[Boris Ferdman]], [[Elias Nehme]], [[Lucien E. Weiss]], [[Reut Orange]], [[Onit Alalouf]] & [[Yoav Shechtman]]\n | title = VIPR: vectorial implementation of phase retrieval for fast and accurate microscopic pixel-wise pupil estimation\n | journal = [[Optics Express]]\n | volume = 28\n | issue = 7\n | pages = 10179\u201310198\n | year = 2020\n | doi = 10.1364/OE.388248\n | pmid = 32225609\n}}\n* {{Cite journal\n | author = [[Naor Granik]], [[Lucien E. Weiss]], [[Elias Nehme]], [[Maayan Levin]], [[Michael Chein]], [[Eran Perlson]], [[Yael Roichman]] & [[Yoav Shechtman]]\n | title = Single-Particle Diffusion Characterization by Deep Learning\n | journal = [[Biophysical Journal]]\n | volume = 117\n | issue = 2\n | pages = 185\u2013192\n | year = 2019\n | doi = 10.1016/j.bpj.2019.06.015\n | pmid = 31280841\n}}\n*{{Cite journal\n | author = [[Eran Hershko]], [[Lucien E. Weiss]], [[Tomer Michaeli]] & [[Yoav Shechtman]]\n | title = Multicolor localization microscopy and point-spread-function engineering by deep learning\n | journal = [[Optics Express]]\n | volume = 27\n | issue = 5\n | pages = 6158\u20136183\n | year = 2019\n | doi = 10.1364/OE.27.006158\n | pmid = 30876208\n}}\n*{{Cite journal\n | author = [[Boris Ferdman]], [[Lucien E. Weiss]], [[Onit Alalouf]], [[Yonathan Haimovich]] & [[Yoav Shechtman]]\n | title = Ultrasensitive Refractometry via Supercritical Angle Fluorescence\n | journal = [[ACS nano]]\n | volume = 12\n | issue = 12\n | pages = 11892\u201311898\n | year = 2018\n | doi = 10.1021/acsnano.8b05849\n | pmid = 30475589\n}}\n*{{Cite journal\n | author = [[Mikael P. Backlund]], [[Yoav Shechtman]] & [[Ronald L. Walsworth]]\n | title = Fundamental Precision Bounds for Three-Dimensional Optical Localization Microscopy with Poisson Statistics\n | journal = [[Physical Review Letters]]\n | volume = 121\n | issue = 2\n | pages = 023904\n | year = 2018\n | doi = 10.1103/PhysRevLett.121.023904\n | pmid = 30085695\n}}\n*{{Cite journal\n | author = [[Anna-Karin Gustavsson]], [[Petar N. Petrov]], [[Maurice Y. Lee]], [[Yoav Shechtman]] & [[W. E. Moerner]]\n | title = Tilted Light Sheet Microscopy with 3D Point Spread Functions for Single-Molecule Super-Resolution Imaging in Mammalian Cells\n | journal = [[Proceedings of SPIE--the International Society for Optical Engineering]]\n | volume = 10500\n | year = 2018\n | doi = 10.1117/12.2288443\n | pmid = 29681676\n}}\n*{{Cite journal\n | author = [[Anna-Karin Gustavsson]], [[Petar N. Petrov]], [[Maurice Y. Lee]], [[Yoav Shechtman]] & [[W. E. Moerner]]\n | title = 3D single-molecule super-resolution microscopy with a tilted light sheet\n | journal = [[Nature Communications]]\n | volume = 9\n | issue = 1\n | pages = 123\n | year = 2018\n | doi = 10.1038/s41467-017-02563-4\n | pmid = 29317629\n}}\n*{{Cite journal\n | author = [[Yoav Shechtman]], [[Anna-Karin Gustavsson]], [[Petar N. Petrov]], [[Elisa Dultz]], [[Maurice Y. Lee]], [[Karsten Weis]] & [[W. E. Moerner]]\n | title = Observation of live chromatin dynamics in cells via 3D localization microscopy using Tetrapod point spread functions\n | journal = [[Biomedical optics express]]\n | volume = 8\n | issue = 12\n | pages = 5735\u20135748\n | year = 2017\n | doi = 10.1364/BOE.8.005735\n | pmid = 29296501\n}}\n*{{Cite journal\n | author = [[Petar N. Petrov]], [[Yoav Shechtman]] & [[W. E. Moerner]]\n | title = Measurement-based estimation of global pupil functions in 3D localization microscopy\n | journal = [[Optics Express]]\n | volume = 25\n | issue = 7\n | pages = 7945\u20137959\n | year = 2017\n | doi = 10.1364/OE.25.007945\n | pmid = 28380911\n}}\n*{{Cite journal\n | author = [[Alex von Diezmann]], [[Yoav Shechtman]] & [[W. E. Moerner]]\n | title = Three-Dimensional Localization of Single Molecules for Super-Resolution Imaging and Single-Particle Tracking\n | journal = [[Chemical 