|title=''It's Pony'' Episode Listings|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Zap2it\">{{cite web|url=https://tvschedule.zap2it.com/overview.html?programSeriesId=SH03391255&tabName=guide&season=1|title=''It's Pony'' Episode Guide|publisher=[[Zap2it]]}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|tt11416026}}\n\n{{Portal|Nickelodeon|Cartoon|Animation|Television}}\n{{Nickelodeon original series}}\n\n[[Category:2020s British animated television series]]\n[[Category:2020s British children's television series]]\n[[Category:2020 British television series debuts]]\n[[Category:British animated television programmes featuring anthropomorphic characters]]\n[[Category:British children's animated adventure television series]]\n[[Category:British children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:British flash animated television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Nickelodeon shows]]\n[[Category:2020s Nickelodeon shows]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about children]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about families]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about horses]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name          = It's Pony\n| image              = It's Pony logo.png\n| genre              = Adventure<br>Children's animated comedy\n| creator            = Ant Blades\n| writer             = {{unbulleted list|Ant Blades|Magda Liolis|Bob Mittenthal|Tobi Wilson|Adam Cohen}}\n| director           = Ant Blades\n| voices             = {{plainlist |\n* [[Jessica DiCicco]]\n* [[Josh Zuckerman]]\n* [[Abraham Benrubi|Abe Benrubi]]\n* [[India de Beaufort]]\n}}\n| opentheme          = {{theme_song|\"It's Pony!\"|Jon Wygens}}\n| composer           = Mike Rubino\n| executive_producer = \n| producer           = {{plainlist |\n* Adam Shaw\n* Denise Green\n}}\n| country            = United Kingdom<br>United States\n| editor             = \n| language           = English\n| network            = [[Nickelodeon]]\n| company            = [[Blue-Zoo Productions|Blue-Zoo Animation]]\n| distributor        = [[ViacomCBS Domestic Media Networks]] \n| num_seasons        = 1<!-- increment when new season begins -->\n| num_episodes       = 9 (18 segments)<!-- increment when new episode airs -->\n| list_episodes      = \n| runtime            = 11 minutes\n| picture_format     = [[HDTV]] [[1080i]]\n| audio_format       = [[Dolby Digital]]\n| first_aired        = {{Start date|2020|1|18}}\n| last_aired         = present\n}}\n'''''It's Pony''''' is a British<!--Blue-Zoo is British, other nationalities must be sourced--> [[animated television series]] created by Ant Blades and storyboarded, designed and animated in England by [[Blue-Zoo Productions|Blue-Zoo Animation]] for [[Nickelodeon]]. The series premiered in the United States on January 18, 2020.\n\n==Plot==\nIt's Pony follows the life of Annie as she does her best to cope in her parent's farm (located on the balcony of their apartment) to the everyday struggles of being a 9-year old in the city. Luckily, she has a pony. He may not be the best pony, but he's hers and she loves him. Pony adores her, but his optimism and enthusiasm often land the pair in unexpected and unwanted situations.\n\n==Characters==\n===Main===\n* Annie (voiced by [[Jessica DiCicco]])<ref name=\"Premiere PR\" />\n* Pony (voiced by [[Josh Zuckerman]])<ref name=\"Premiere PR\" />\n* Dad (voiced by [[Abraham Benrubi|Abe Benrubi]])<ref name=\"Premiere PR\" />\n* Mom (voiced by [[India de Beaufort]])<ref name=\"Premiere PR\" />\n\n===Supporting===\n* Fred (voiced by [[Kal Penn]])<ref name=\"Premiere PR\" />\n* Brian (voiced by [[Bobby Moynihan]])<ref name=\"Premiere PR\" />\n* Ms. Ramiro (voiced by [[Rosario Dawson]])<ref name=\"Premiere PR\" />\n* Mr. Pancks (voiced by [[Mark Feuerstein]])<ref name=\"Premiere PR\" />\n* Beatrice (voiced by [[Megan Hilty]])<ref name=\"Premiere PR\" />\n* Clara (voiced by Taylor Polidore)\n* Heston (voiced by [[Josh Keaton]])\n* Henrietta (voiced by [[Grey Griffin]])\n* Gerry (voiced by Noshir Dalal)\n* Carl\n* Leanne (voiced by [[Anjali Bhimani]])\n\n== Production ==\nOn March 6, 2018, it was announced that [[Nickelodeon]] officially [[green-lit]] the series with a 20-episode order at Nickelodeon's 2018 upfront presentation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/nick-2018-upfront-original-pony-loud-house-spin-off-blues-clues-remake-coming-soon|title=Nick Upfront 2018: Original ''Pony'', ''Loud House'' Spin-Off, ''Blue's Clues'' Remake Coming Soon|website=[[Animation Magazine]]|date=March 6, 2018|access-date=March 6, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2018/03/06/nickelodeon-greenlights-original-animated-comedy-series-pony-241010/20180306nickelodeon01/|title=Nickelodeon Greenlights Original Animated Comedy Series ''Pony''|publisher=[[Nickelodeon]]|via=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=March 6, 2018|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2018/03/06/nickelodeon-unveils-content-pipeline-of-more-than-800-new-episodes-details-expansion-into-location-based-and-vr-experiences-881312/20180306nickelodeon08/|title=Nickelodeon Unveils Content Pipeline of More Than 800 New Episodes, Details Expansion into Location-Based and VR Experiences|publisher=[[Nickelodeon]]|via=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=March 6, 2018|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref> On December 9, 2019, it was announced that the series would premiere on January 18, 2020, with a teaser episode released online on December 26, 2019.<ref name=\"Premiere PR\">{{cite press release|title=Nickelodeon Debuts Brand-New Animated Series, ''It\u2019s Pony,'' Saturday, Jan. 18|url=https://www.nickpress.com/press-releases/2019/12/09/nickelodeon-debuts-brand-new-animated-series-its-pony-saturday-jan-18|publisher=Nickelodeon Press|date=December 9, 2019|access-date=December 9, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/pets/its-pony-nickelodeon-sneak-peek/|title=New Series Spotlights the Sweet Bond Between a Girl and Her Horse: Check Out ''It's Pony''|website=[[People (magazine)|People]]|last=Hogan|first=Kate|date=December 9, 2019|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{Episode table \n|background=#FF5F5F \n|overall= \n|title=\n|titleR=<ref name=\"The Futon Critic\" /><ref name=\"Zap2it\" />\n|writer= \n|aux2= \n|aux2T=Storyboard by\n|airdate=\n|airdateR=<ref name=\"The Futon Critic\" /><ref name=\"Zap2it\" />\n|prodcode= \n|prodcodeR=<ref name=\"The Futon Critic\" />\n|viewers= \n|country=U.S. \n|episodes= \n\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| Title               = Nosy Pony\"<hr />\"Beatrice\n| WrittenBy           = Ant Blades, Magda Liolis<br />and Bob Mittenthal\n| Aux2                = Francesca Adams & Catherine Salkeld<hr />Charlie Higson & Denzel De Meerleer\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|1|18}}\n| ProdCode            = 102\n| Viewers             = 0.96<ref name=\"1-01\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-1-18-2020.html|title=Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 1.18.2020|work=[[Showbuzz Daily]]|author=[[Mitch Metcalf]]|date=January 22, 2020|access-date=January 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary        = \"Nosy Pony\": In order to run the family's produce stand, Annie tries to get Pony to stop being nosy.\n\n\"Beatrice\": Annie lets Pony spend the day with her friend Beatrice, but worries that Beatrice is better at caring for Pony than herself.\n| LineColor           = FF5F5F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 2<hr />3\n| Title               = Unicorn<hr />Plants!\n| WrittenBy           = Ant Blades, Magda Liolis<br />and Bob Mittenthal\n| Aux2                = Charlie Higson & Dan Hamman<hr />Francesca Adams & Denzel De Meerleer\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|1|25}}{{efn|name=episode3date|\"Plants!\" was released on the Nick App and Nick On Demand 